{"session_id":"svc-1781394379028793291","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-06-13T23:46:19.93744126Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-3141b561-20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add` only for legitimate child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges; never the parent.\u0026#xA;3. Use `parent=\u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` metadata and wire `parent -\u0026gt; child`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Don\u0026#39;t mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; don\u0026#39;t parallelize `git add`, `git commit`, or staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; subject ends with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add` for child-to-child or sibling/replacement edges, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Long-running matrix/benchmark beads\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For expensive commands (benchmarks, load tests, validation \u0026gt; 60s per variant):\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Write a matrix plan before launching expensive commands: list required configs, output paths, completion criteria.\u0026#xA;- Do not re-run the same long-running command unless: (1) the command fingerprint changed (args/env/config), AND (2) you document why prior output is invalid and what changed.\u0026#xA;- If a long-running command times out or is incomplete, exit with `status: open` + retryable `reason` in `no_changes_rationale.txt`. Do not silently retry; let the orchestrator decide.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-3141b561\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: preserve dirty no-evidence attempts for rescue\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;During dogfood on 2026-06-13, `ddx work --once` for ddx-c02ce93c ran a provider attempt that edited implementation files and exited 0, but produced no commit and no `no_changes_rationale.txt`. DDx reported `no_evidence_produced` with dirty paths, then removed the isolated attempt worktree. The operator could not rescue the provider patch from the worktree and had to manually reimplement from partial observed output. A worker surface that destroys dirty provider output after a successful process exit is not acceptable: DDx must preserve or export recoverable evidence for underspecified provider/commit failures.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1416-1427` classifies clean-exit/no-commit/no-rationale as `task_no_evidence` and records dirty paths, but it does not convert dirty no-evidence into a preserved recoverable attempt.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:943-954` defers attempt cleanup for all non-preserved worktree attempts; because `task_no_evidence` is not preserved, cleanup proceeds.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1577-1588` removes every non-success attempt worktree unless a preserve flag is set, including dirty `task_no_evidence` attempts.\u0026#xA;- `cli/internal/agent/gitops_real.go:35-37` ignores `git worktree remove --force` errors, so cleanup failures would also be underreported.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Treat dirty `task_no_evidence` as recoverable provider output: before cleanup, preserve the worktree with a `refs/ddx/iterations/\u0026lt;bead\u0026gt;/\u0026lt;attempt\u0026gt;` ref or export a patch/artifact that contains every dirty path and enough metadata to reconstruct the attempt. Worker output and bead events must name the preserve ref or patch path. Only clean no-evidence attempts may be removed normally.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;IN-SCOPE FILES\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/gitops_real.go\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_integration_test.go\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_e2e_test.go\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Do not change legitimate `no_changes_rationale.txt` handling. Do not preserve clean no-evidence attempts without dirty paths. Do not kill or change provider subprocess supervision; ddx-c02ce93c handled that separately. Do not hand-edit `.ddx/beads.jsonl`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DOGFOOD EVIDENCE\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Attempt `20260613T225213-a01c938c` for ddx-c02ce93c exited 0 after editing `cli/cmd/work_status_test.go`, `cli/internal/agent/agent_runner_service.go`, `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go`, `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go`, provider child files, liveness/status files, and then DDx deleted `/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-c02ce93c-20260613T225213-a01c938c`.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. `TestExecuteBead_DirtyNoEvidencePreservesAttempt` proves a fake runner that leaves dirty code files, exits 0, and writes no commit/rationale returns `no_evidence_produced` with a non-empty preserve ref or patch artifact instead of deleting the attempt.\u0026#xA;2. `TestExecuteBead_CleanNoEvidenceStillCleansWorktree` proves a clean no-evidence attempt still cleans up normally and does not create a preserve artifact.\u0026#xA;3. `TestWorkLoopNoEvidenceReportsPreserveLocation` proves `ddx work` output/bead event includes the preserve ref or patch path for dirty no-evidence attempts.\u0026#xA;4. `TestRealGitOpsWorktreeRemoveReportsFailure` proves `RealGitOps.WorktreeRemove` returns an error when `git worktree remove --force` fails instead of swallowing it.\u0026#xA;5. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#39;TestExecuteBead_DirtyNoEvidencePreservesAttempt|TestExecuteBead_CleanNoEvidenceStillCleansWorktree|TestWorkLoopNoEvidenceReportsPreserveLocation|TestRealGitOpsWorktreeRemoveReportsFailure\u0026#39; -count=1` passes.\u0026#xA;6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:build, area:agent, area:work, kind:bug, kind:reliability, severity:critical, no-evidence, rescue\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-9d1af129\" base-rev=\"031e75cbf7e60af2e3d4fcf0edaf6a7c5637a6bb\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_ATTEMPT_ID":"20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4","DDX_BEAD_DIR":"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx/.ddx","DDX_BEAD_ID":"ddx-3141b561","DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-3141b561-20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4/.ddx/executions/20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-3141b561-20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4/.ddx/executions/20260613T234600-ed1ce6e4/embedded/git-bin:/Applications/SnowS